From: Lumi Upgrade v1 (orbit-reticle, larger+faster scan-wait mascot)
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] lumiTypes.ts — add 'orbit-reticle' movement mode

Adds a new value to LumiMovementMode so LumiMascot can orbit a screen-coord
center (passed via freePosition) at orbitRadius/orbitSpeedRpm from the state
profile. Used by ScanScreen during evaluation to orbit the viewfinder reticle.

Pure additive change. Existing 'anchor' | 'wander' | 'drift' callers unaffected.

---
 components/Lumi/lumiTypes.ts | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/components/Lumi/lumiTypes.ts b/components/Lumi/lumiTypes.ts
--- a/components/Lumi/lumiTypes.ts
+++ b/components/Lumi/lumiTypes.ts
@@ -50,7 +50,11 @@ export type LumiPosition =
 export type LumiMovementMode =
   | 'anchor'       // stay at preset position (original behavior)
   | 'wander'       // smooth figure-8 across upper portion of screen
-  | 'drift';       // gentle horizontal drift along an edge
+  | 'drift'        // gentle horizontal drift along an edge
+  | 'orbit-reticle'; // v6.5 — orbit a screen-coord center (passed via
+                   //         freePosition) at orbitRadius/orbitSpeedRpm
+                   //         from the active state's animation profile.
+                   //         Used during scan-evaluation to orbit the viewfinder.
 
 // ─── Theme variants ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 
